98/Math/MathML"{$><$}mml:mi{$>$}C{$<$}/mml:mi{$><$}/mml:math{$>$} depend on the change in average trait value and therefore cannot predict that change. In this formulation, which has been called ``exact and general'' by its proponents, Hamilton's rule can ``predict'' only the data that have already been given.},
